node.text:
Captain Chelsey Sullenberger and First Officer Jeffery Skiles saved all 155 people onboard US Airways Flight 1549 after the successfully crash landing on the Hudson River in what would become to be known as the miracle on the Hudson. 

Video: @maxlangleyimages 
Media: Con Edison, AFP News, Live ATC Clips, Inc., AliasAnimo, Port Authority New York & New Jersey, ABC News, Wikimedia
Thumbnail: Carolinas Aviation Museum

node.text:
United Airlines (UA) has reached an agreement with the Air Line Pilots Association (ALPA) to prevent the furlough of close to 3,000 pilots. The deal has been agreed in principle and is still to be approved by the leadership of the ALPA UA chapter.

Link to article: https://airwaysmag.com/airlines/ua-pilots-union-agree-to-deal-avoid-furloughs/

Video: Max Langley (@maxlangleyimages)
Media: United Airlines
Thumbnail: Liam Funnell (@downwindaviation_)

And, this may be a first for our page! ✈

"Air shows always offer a unique chance to see rare and special airplanes that you are normally unable to see. This was my first opportunity to get a good shot of the P-51 and as it flexed on takeoff right in front of me I was able to capture this beauty of a shot!"

📸 Let's introduce this week's featured photographer. This week, It is Jack O’Brien (@deltacs100)!

So, let's get started!

"Hey everyone, my name is Jack O’Brien, I’m an Atlanta based plane spotter. I have had passion for aviation for my whole life. I got into plane spotting last May and I been hooked ever since. To start off I have a United 787-10 climbing out of Atlanta during golden hour with a stunning backdrop!"

node.text:
⏮ The past week has been filled with plenty of news as well as interesting articles. So, let's look back at a few of them. 

As always, if you haven't already, make sure to check them out! ✈ 

🌍 Defaulted Etihad-Linked Bonds Receive Low Bids,
